Diagram illustrating a Digital Transformation (DT) assessment and roadmap framework consisting of three sections.

Section 1 – Enterprise DTA: Evaluates DT readiness across 5 dimensions: Customer Understandings, Strategy and Leadership, Technology and Infrastructure, Operations, and People, Organization and Culture. Assessment is conducted via online survey, resulting in DT Level and Implication reports for each dimension.

Section 2 – Manufacturing Assessment: Evaluates the business value-chain including Purchasing, R&D, Marketing, Production, Logistics, Sales, Service, and Management. Also conducted via online survey, producing Assessment Results combined with As-Is Analysis and Best Practice benchmarking, resulting in DT Level and Implication reports for each business process.

Section 3 – DT Roadmap (Illustrative): A 3-stage progression. Stage 1: Implement DT Capability and Infrastructure. Stage 2: Data-driven Business Innovation. Stage 3: Global Leader with DT. Strategic focus areas include: Maximize the Experience and Value of Customer and Employee; Innovate How You Work by Digitizing Business Operations; Optimize Infrastructure based on Digital Technology; Sustainable DT Change Management.

Business Expectations listed at the bottom: Assess digital readiness at corporate level and define implications; Assess digital maturity for business processes and define improvement opportunities; Establish DT strategy, roadmap, and implementation plans.




Diagram illustrating a Cloud Assessment and Consulting framework structured in three layers.

Layer 1 – Cloud Assessment: Evaluates five areas in sequence: Strategy and Organization, Process, Governance and Skill, Architecture and Infrastructure, and Platform and Application.

Layer 2 – Cloud Consulting: Four sequential consulting phases: As-Is Analysis, Setup Direction, Define To-Be Model, and Establish Action Plan.

Layer 3 – Blue Print for DT (Cloud based): Four outcome areas with corresponding initiatives.
First, Data-driven Business Innovation: Increase network bandwidth; Secure large cloud storage.
Second, R&D Support: Improve R&D portal for cooperation; Utilize customized cloud resources.
Third, Smart Work Environment: Flexible smart work environment; Integrated software management; Enhance Security.
Fourth, Business Continuity: Cloud Scalability and Elasticity when and wherever required; Extend DR System based on SDDC.

Business Expectations listed at the bottom: Design R&D supporting infrastructure concept model to enhance manufacturing capability; Build high-scalable and high-use IT platform based on cloud technology; Integrated management of cloud resources by establishing governance.

